column1: #Text=Tega Cay is a small city along the eastern shore of Lake Wylie west of the town of Fort Mill in the Olde English District of South Carolina .
#Text=Tega Cay is a suburb of the major city of Charlotte and has experienced rapid growth over the past decade .

#Text=Cay means " beautiful peninsula " in Polynesian and has been known for its professional golf courses , restaurants and beachfront parks located on the Tega Cay peninsula of Lake Wylie in South Carolina .
#Text=Cay is accessible from Interstate-485 exit number 4 and Interstate-77 exit number 88 .
#Text=Tega Cay is best accessed by car , but cycling is common through the town especially in residential areas of the greater peninsula .
